column5: Was on a bird/photography site and someone found this today on shore.  Apparently it is a Grebe that's eyes were bigger than it's stomach.
That's exactly what I  look like after every Thanksgiving meal Joey
I find this pic funnier than I probably should.
You know how fast the walleye was moving when he hit the bird?
Yes, it's is creepily amazing were my thoughts!
Mom, "see what happens when you don't chew your food well!" Son, "yes, mom"  Furthermore, what was he thinking???

Red-necked grebe, winter plumage. They're not the only ones who make mistakes, I've heard a credible witness who found a dead Great Blue heron with a stick lodged in its throat after mistaking it for a fish. We don't have the insult 'bird brain' for nothing.
